    • getAsBoolean

      public boolean getAsBoolean(@Nonnull String name, boolean defaultValue)
      Fetch a value of the attributes and convert it to a boolean value. This method will return the default value in case its not absolutely clear what boolean value is stored with the supplied attribute name.
      Parameters:
      name - name of attribute
      defaultValue - default value
      Returns:
      the boolean value stored or the default value

    • getAsInteger

      public int getAsInteger(@Nonnull String name)
      Fetch a value from the attributes and convert it to a integer.
      Parameters:
      name - the name of the attribute
      Returns:
      the number stored with the supplied name
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - in case the name argument can't be resolved to a value
      NumberFormatException - in case the value of the requested attribute does not contain a integer number

    • getAsInteger

      public int getAsInteger(@Nonnull String name, int defaultValue)
      Fetch a value from the attributes and convert it to a integer. The default value is returned in case the attribute name can't be mapped to a value or the value can't be converted to a integer.
      Parameters:
      name - the attribute name
      defaultValue - the value returned in case the attribute can't be converted to a integer value
      Returns:
      the integer representation of the attribute value or the default value
